answers.body_markdown:
You have to bind keys from `applicationHost.properties` as `String` rather than `Properties`. For example, if you have key `appsDeployedProperties` in `applicationHost.properties`, as follows:

**applicationHost.properties**

    appsDeployedProperties=hello

In Spring Bean, you have to use as String, like:

    @Value(&quot;#{appsDeployedProperties}&quot;)
    private String appsDeployedProperties;


P.S: You can add `ignoreUnresolvablePlaceholders` key with value as `true` to tell Spring to ignore keys used in bean which are not mentioned in any property file, as follows:

    &lt;bean id=&quot;applicationHostProperties&quot;
            class=&quot;org.springframework.beans.factory.config.PropertiesFactoryBean&quot;&gt;
            &lt;property name=&quot;ignoreResourceNotFound&quot; value=&quot;true&quot;&gt;&lt;/property&gt;
    		&lt;property name=&quot;ignoreUnresolvablePlaceholders&quot; value=&quot;true&quot;/&gt;
            &lt;property name=&quot;locations&quot;&gt;
                &lt;list&gt;
                    &lt;value&gt;classpath:applicationHost.properties&lt;/value&gt;
                &lt;/list&gt;
            &lt;/property&gt;
    &lt;/bean&gt;

