I&#39;ve figured out what is causing this. The test is closing the server before the ObjectMapper has converted the object into JSON.

To fix this I used a `BlockingQueue` in my test and polled for 1 second after sending the message. 

    BlockingQueue&lt;String&gt; blockingQueue = new ArrayBlockingQueue(1);

    stompSession.subscribe(&quot;/topic/greetings&quot;, new StompFrameHandler() {

        @Override
        public Type getPayloadType(StompHeaders headers) {
            return String.class;
        }

        @Override
        public void handleFrame(StompHeaders headers, Object payload) {
            System.out.println(&quot;Received message: &quot; + payload);

        }
    });

    stompSession.send(&quot;/app/welcome/test&quot;, &quot;Mike&quot;);
    blockingQueue.poll(1, SECONDS);

